From a2ffe10eb6fc799a502f0acf24e19adec0705380 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Wed, 19 Nov 2025 19:05:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 07/74] FEDORA: Fixed the udev rules file
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Also:
  - move 56-hpmud.rules into main package completely (bug #1033952)
  - run autoreconf instead of patching libtool script to work-around rpath issues

    There's been a libhpdiscovery since 3.15.11, which messes up builds
    when we remove rpath from libtool script.
    Running autoreconf seems to work-around the problem.
  - Don't specify python version in hplip-printer@.service (bug #1266423)
  - ship hp-config_usb_printer in main package along with udev rule and unit file (#1033952#11)
  - --enable-udev-acl-rules configure flag has been removed upstream
  - change udev rule to not add printer queue, just check plugin
  - Really move udev rules to /lib/udev/rules.d (bug #748208).
  - Removed SYSFS use in udev rules and actually made them work (bug
    #560754).
  - Don't ship udev rules; instead, grant an ACL for group lp (bug #424331).
  - Adjusted udev rules to be less permissive. We use ConsoleKit to add ACLs
    to the device nodes, so world-writable device nodes can be avoided.
  - Updated udev rules to allow scanning by console user (reverted)
  - Fixed the udev rules file (bug #248740, bug #249025).

Signed-off-by: Zdenek Dohnal <zdohnal@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Jaromír Končický <jkoncick@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Jiří Popelka <jpopelka@fedoraproject.org>

Link: https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/hplip/blob/b77fb66d568d2beb930147d87e74caed93ed3e85/f/hplip-udev-rules.patch
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 Makefile.am | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile.am b/Makefile.am
index 605744a..5381a24 100644
--- a/Makefile.am
+++ b/Makefile.am
@@ -137,7 +137,7 @@ dist_rulessystem_DATA =data/rules/hplip-printer@.service
 
 # hpmud.rules
 if !HPLIP_CLASS_DRIVER
-rulesdir = /etc/udev/rules.d
+rulesdir = /usr/lib/udev/rules.d
 if UDEV_SYSFS_RULES
 dist_rules_DATA = data/rules/56-hpmud_sysfs.rules
 else
